===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ja|en}} {{m|ja|sc=Jpan|将軍|tr=shōgun}}, from an abbreviation of {{m|ja|sc=Jpan|征夷大将軍|tr=Seii Taishogun}} which means "General who overcomes the barbarians", from {{etyl|ltc|en}} [[將]][[軍]] (''tsjàng-kjun'' "leader of troops", "general") (compare {{etyl|cmn|en}} ''jiàngjūn'' 将军).

